s exhaust him.This edition features stunning facsimiles of the diary’s pages accompanied by an English translation, an extensive historical introduction, numerous illustrations, and editorial annotations. Supplementary materials include letters, postcards, statements, and speeches as well as a chronology, a bibliography, and an index.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh  a1922–1923.  aAlbert Einstein.  aArgentina.  aBrazil.  aBuenos Aires.  aEinstein enthuses about the stunning vistas of lush vegetation in Rio de Janeiro.  aEinstein the person.  aEinstein wrote in journal.  aEinstein's diary.  aEinstein's journal.  aEinstein’s musings on science.  aPrinceton University press.  aSouth America travel diary.  aSouth America, 1925.  aSpain.  aSupplementary materials.  aThe Travel Diaries of Albert Einstein.  aUruguay.  aZe’ev Rosenkranz.  aa bibliography.  aadmiration for the Uruguayans.  aan index.  aart.  abiography.  abooks about Albert Einstein.  achronology.  aeditorial annotations.  ahumanitarian icon.  aletters.  along ocean voyages.  ameetings with other prominent colleagues and statesmen.  anumerous illustrations.  aphilosophy.  apolitics.  apostcards.  apreeminent scientist.  aspeeches.  astatements.  atelegraphic-style diary entries.  athe inner thoughts of Einstein.  athe life of Albert Einstein.  athree month journey.1 aRosenkranz, Ze’ev, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107497480 cprintz978069120102340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691242507?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691242507423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97